<body>
	<div class="container" style="padding:20px;width:800px !important; height: 900px !important;">
		<p style="align: center; font-size: 25px;"><b>Flying Fox 1.0 B2C E-Commerce System</b></p>
		<p style="align: center; font-size: 16px;">Flying Fox is a B2B and B2C ecommerce platform that attached payment gateway with local well established first and third party acquirers such as Paynet, government agency under Bank Negara Malaysia. </p>
		<p style="align: center;"><img src="/images/cprofile/Screenshot_from_2017-10-06_13-21-44.png" style="width: 100%" /> </p>
		<p style="align: center;"><img src="/images/cprofile/Screenshot_from_2017-10-06_13-52-33.png" style="width: 100%" /> </p>
		<p style="float: left;"><img src="/images/cprofile/circle1.png" /> </p><p style="align: center; font-size: 16px;"><b>Product Menu:</b></p>
		<p style="font-size: 16px;">This includes a tab for O-Shop, Retail for online B2C, B2B for dealers purchase, Voucher (future feature), and Hyper for group buy.</p>
		<div class="clearfix"></div>
		<p style="float: left;"><img src="/images/cprofile/circle2.png" /> </p><p style="align: center; font-size: 16px;"><b>Product Likes:</b></p>
		<p style="font-size: 16px;">Tracks who had liked the products.</p>
		<div class="clearfix"></div>
		<p style="float: left;"><img src="/images/cprofile/circle3.png" /> </p><p style="align: center; font-size: 16px;"><b>Add Cart:</b></p>
		<p style="font-size: 16px;">Standard shopping cart, when buyer wants to buy a product.</p>
		<div class="clearfix"></div>
		<p style="float: left;"><img src="/images/cprofile/circle4.png" /> </p><p style="align: center; font-size: 16px;"><b>OpenWish:</b></p>
		<p style="font-size: 16px;">Allows a buyer to participate in creating an OpenWish and letting his friends know of what he likes via all the supported social media platforms.</p>
		<div class="clearfix"></div>
		<p style="float: left;"><img src="/images/cprofile/circle5.png" /> </p><p style="align: center; font-size: 16px;"><b>Social Media Marketeer:</b></p>
		<p style="font-size: 16px;">Allows a buyer to participate in helping merchants to advertise their products and services via the buyer’s social media account. Upon a successful transaction, the buyer gets commission.</p>
		<div class="clearfix"></div>
		<p style="float: left;"><img src="/images/cprofile/circle6.png" /> </p><p style="align: center; font-size: 16px;"><b>QR Code:</b></p>
		<p style="font-size: 16px;">Once scanned, brings the user directly to the product information view.</p>
		<div class="clearfix"></div>
		<p style="align: center;"><img src="/images/cprofile/Screenshot_from_2017-10-06_15-18-49.png" style="width: 100%" /> </p>
		<p style="align: center;"><img src="/images/cprofile/Screenshot_from_2017-10-06_15-19-10.png" style="width: 100%" /> </p>
		<p style="align: center;"><img src="/images/cprofile/Screenshot_from_2017-10-06_15-22-16.png" style="width: 100%" /> </p>
		<p style="align: center;"><img src="/images/cprofile/Screenshot_from_2017-10-06_15-33-40.png" style="width: 100%" /> </p>
		<p style="float: left;"><img src="/images/cprofile/circle1.png" /> </p><p style="align: center; font-size: 16px;"><b>Graphical Status View (Longnose):</b></p>
		<p style="font-size: 16px;">This is the graphical respresentation of the entire online B2C buying process, which includes a product return process initiated by the buyer. This new system, totally does away with the manual use of AirwayBill (AWB)/Consignment No. for tracking via the individual courier’s portal. OpenSupermall embeds all information in this compact graphical view. No knowledge of the AWB number is required, as integration has been done which facilitates system to system communication with the logistic provider.</p>
		<div class="clearfix"></div>
		<p style="float: left;"><img src="/images/cprofile/circle2.png" /> </p><p style="align: center; font-size: 16px;"><b>Pending:</b></p>
		<p style="font-size: 16px;">The starting point of online B2C buying process, after payment has complete, and awaiting for the seller (merchant) to acknowledge and start processing the deal.</p>
		<div class="clearfix"></div>
		<p style="float: left;"><img src="/images/cprofile/circle3.png" /> </p><p style="align: center; font-size: 16px;"><b>Delivery Attempts:</b></p>
		<p style="font-size: 16px;">This records the number of delivery attempts by the courier or logistic provider. A time and date stamp is recorded for each attempt and is toggle displayed on the interface itself. 3 delivery attempts are supported, after which package shall be returned to sender.</p>
		<div class="clearfix"></div>
		<p style="float: left;"><img src="/images/cprofile/circle4.png" /> </p><p style="align: center; font-size: 16px;"><b>Return Goods Process:</b></p>
		<p style="font-size: 16px;">When a buyer is not satisfied with his purchase for any reason, he/she has the right to request for a return or refund. OpenSupermall’s return process or procedure is fully online, and does not require either the buyer or seller to use the phone or email for communication. All information exchanges are done via the system using intuitive interfaces. Upon initiated, this return process is depicted on the Longnose interface as a green line.</p>
		<div class="clearfix"></div>
		<p style="float: left;"><img src="/images/cprofile/circle5.png" /> </p><p style="align: center; font-size: 16px;"><b>Merchant Approved:</b></p>
		<p style="font-size: 16px;">Once the merchant receives the returned goods, he can make an informed decision based on remarks or complaints given by the buyer in addition to any photographs or images which the buyer may include with the return request. </p>
		<div class="clearfix"></div>
		<p style="float: left;"><img src="/images/cprofile/circle6.png" /> </p><p style="align: center; font-size: 16px;"><b>Proof-of-Delivery To Buyer:</b></p>
		<p style="font-size: 16px;">Once the goods has been delivered to the buyer’s address or location, the buyer or a representative would need to electronically sign-off and give basic identification via the delivery personnel mobile device. Note that these data is available after actual input in a matter of seconds, in real time, as long as Internet access is available.  These shall serve as a proof-of-delivery. </p>
		<div class="clearfix"></div>	
		<p style="float: left;"><img src="/images/cprofile/circle6.png" /> </p><p style="align: center; font-size: 16px;"><b>Proof-of-Delivery To Merchant::</b></p>
		<p style="font-size: 16px;">This happens during a return process when a buyer sends goods back to the seller. The process is exactly the same during delivery to buyer, just the addresses are reversed. For this, the seller’s representative shall sign-off and provide the basic identification. These data will be displayed here. </p>
		<div class="clearfix"></div>		
	</div>
</body>
